          <li>Witnesses (shahid) with their details</li>
          <li>Mehr (dower amount) agreed upon</li>
          <li>Date of marriage (Islamic and Gregorian calendar)</li>
          <li>Location where Nikah was performed</li>
          <li>Nikah Registrar or Qazi signature and stamp</li>
          <li>Union Council registration number</li>
          <li>Any special conditions agreed in the contract</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <p>Most Nikah Nama documents are written in Urdu. Some contain Arabic religious phrases and Quranic references. Older certificates often have handwritten sections that can be difficult to read.</p>

